Medical Chatbot using Meta Llama 2 Large Language Model

Vaishnavi Shankar Devadig, 2024

Llama 2 Family:¶

Llama 2 is a family of models, both pre-trained and fine-tuned that find most of their use cases in the field of Natural Language Processing, mostly text generation. The maximum context length here is 4096 token, which implies that the model can remember the context of a maximum of 4096 tokens while spitting out solutions. The Llama 2 models were also trained with RLHF (Reinforcement Learning with human feedback) that makes it perform better is case of human beliefs.

This project specifically uses Llama 2 family's 7B Chat model.¶

Langchain Framework:¶

LangChain is a versatile framework designed for easily building and deploying language model applications. It simplifies integrating large language models with data sources and search engines, enabling the development of advanced natural language processing (NLP) applications. With support for functionalities like document retrieval, question answering, and text summarization, LangChain leverages popular NLP models and services to enhance development efficiency.

Pinecone Vectore Database:¶

Pinecone is a cutting-edge, cloud-native vector database that excels in handling high-dimensional vector data through Approximate Nearest Neighbor (ANN) search, optimizing for speed, accuracy, and performance in complex and large datasets. It revolutionizes data storage and retrieval by efficiently indexing and searching for the most similar vectors, enabling fast, real-time updates and searches across billions of items. With features like filtered search, backups, and a user-friendly API supporting multiple programming languages, Pinecone stands out for its scalability, security, and cost-effectiveness.
